			<abstract>
				<p>Testimony of Estera Stern, who was taken from the Sosnowiec Ghetto in February 1943 to a labor camp in Parschnitz near Trutnov. She
					describes conditions in the camp and forced labor in the Trutnov textile factory. She was liberated by the Red Army on May 8,
					1945.</p>
			</abstract>
